# TASK_PACKET

Task ID
CRUSHR-FORMAT-11

Title
Test distributed extent-identity headers as a manifest-minimizing recovery architecture

Role
BUILDER

Objective
Implement a bounded experimental archive variant that replaces most global file-manifest dependency with small distributed per-extent identity headers, then compare recovery capability and archive size against existing FORMAT-10 variants.

The purpose of this packet is to test whether crushr can preserve current salvage behavior with a more elegant and less size-heavy structure:

- payload extents carry enough local identity to self-group
- global manifest responsibility is reduced or eliminated
- recovery becomes payload-structure-first instead of manifest-first

This is an experiment.
It must not silently change default archive behavior.

