Context

FORMAT-10 demonstrated:

- full_current_experimental and payload_plus_manifest both achieve 12 named recoveries
- payload_only and payload_plus_path achieve only 2 named recoveries
- full_current_experimental doubles archive size vs payload_only
- payload_plus_manifest is materially smaller than full_current_experimental while preserving named recovery

This suggests:
- recovery needs file-structure truth
- path-only metadata is weak
- the full metadata stack is unnecessary
- the manifest may currently be acting as a large global structure map

The next hypothesis to test:

Can distributed per-extent identity headers provide enough file-structure truth to recover files without a large global manifest?

